This guy knows shit. Journalists have written whole books since 2010 talking about the corruption of Genaro García Luna, the head of security in México from 2006 to 2012. The arrest of this guy was a result of the testimony of Vicente "vicentillo" Zambada captured in 2009. Vicentillo Zambada is the son of "el mayo" Zambada, the real head of the Cartel of sinaloa and "compadre" of el Chapo.
This guy talks about facts that are in public records coming from trials in the US like he was an insider. And el Chapo became a DEA informant since 1998 during his first time in jail, that's why he became the legend he Is now after his first jail escape in 2001, he used extra help from the DEA to kill or sent to jail the members of the cartel of Los Beltrán Leyva, los Zetas, la Familia Michoacana: the enemys of the cartel of Sinaloa. Vicentillo Zambada used this information to avoid life in prison and also testified against his father and his compadre el chapo, and in exchange he got sentencend to just 15 years in 2019...and taking into accout he was already served 10 years in prison waiting for his sentence, the year un prison un México awaiting his extradition to the US, good conduct and such...he must be roaming free as a protected witness in US territory
